{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, when evaluated at R max, the performance of pinocchio approaches that of the neural networks, although it still shows larger scatter.",
    "In conclusion, the neural networks consistently outperform pinocchio, particularly for low-mass halos and within R Lag, while preserving the qualitative behavior observed in the ground truth distributions.",
    "Figure 10 presents spherically averaged radial profiles for three representative proto-halos (H1, H2, H3; left to right), illustrating how model performance varies with distance from the true center of mass.",
    "The rows correspond to four metrics: accuracy, FPR, completeness, and purity (top to bottom).",
    "Different linestyles denote the models: solid for vipr, dashed for copra, and dotted for pinocchio."
  ]
}